.TH _PRINTF 3 "27 Novembre 2025" "Version 1.0" "Holberton School"
.SH NAME
_printf \- custom formatted output conversion function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.P
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf
function is a custom implementation of the standard C library
.BR printf (3)
function. It produces output according to a format string that can contain format specifiers.
.P
The function writes formatted output to the standard output stream (stdout). It processes the format string character by character, recognizing conversion specifiers that begin with a percent sign (%) and replacing them with the corresponding argument values.
.SH SUPPORTED CONVERSION SPECIFIERS
The following conversion specifiers are supported:
.TP
.B %c
Print a single character. Takes an integer argument and outputs the corresponding character.
.TP
.B %s
Print a null-terminated string. Takes a pointer to a character string and outputs all characters until the null terminator. If the pointer is NULL, outputs "(null)".
.TP
.B %d
Print a signed integer in decimal format. Supports negative numbers.
.TP
.B %i
Print a signed integer in decimal format (identical to %d).
.TP
.B %%
Print a literal percent sign (%). Does not consume any arguments.
.SH UNSUPPORTED FEATURES
The following features are
.B not
supported in this implementation:
.P
- Flag characters (-, +, 0, space, #)
.br
- Field width specifications
.br
- Precision specifications
.br
- Length modifiers (h, l, L)
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.B _printf
function returns the total number of characters successfully printed to stdout. This count excludes the null terminator.
.P
If an error occurs, the function returns \-1.
.SH EXAMPLES
.B Basic Usage:
.br
_printf("Hello, World!\\n");
.P
.B Printing a character:
.br
_printf("Character: %c\\n", 'A');
.br
Output: Character: A
.P
.B Printing an integer:
.br
_printf("Value: %i\\n", 100);
.br
Output: Value: 100
.P
.B Handling NULL strings:
.br
_printf("String: %s\\n", NULL);
.br
Output: String: (null)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3),
.BR write (2)
.SH AUTHORS
Written by Hugo Ramos (hugou74130) and Sara Rebati (SaraEstelle).